name: untitled map no. 1305-25
description:
Original work on paper by Portland, Ore. artist Thérèse Murdza.

Made with professional-grade watercolor, acrylic, ink, graphite, water-soluable pencil and/or crayon on Arches cold-pressed watercolor paper. 

Part of a series created with collected rainwater (really), as part of Portland's Recycled Rain Project.

10" x 8" paper size (13” x 15” framed).

Custom framing in partnership with Luke’s Frame Shop, Portland, Ore.

Please keep artwork protected from prolonged, direct sunlight.

Artist signature on back.

Free shipping within the US. Estimated arrival 5-7 days from order date. Contact us for speedier service and/or international delivery. Studio pick-up available for Portland-local.

All images ©2013 Thérèse Murdza.
All rights reserved forever. And ever. xo

name: [PRINT] there is convexity in her claim
description:
Reproduction print of an original painting on canvas by Thérèse Murdza.

Created in collaboration with the digital imaging experts at Portland's pushdot studio (pushdotstudio.com), and printed using archival pigment-based inks on fine art paper for longevity.

All images printed with a minimum 1" border.

Custom sizes and substrates available upon request.

Artist signature on back. 

Small prints ship flat; larger prints ship rolled. Estimated arrival 7-14 days from order date. Contact us for speedier service.

All images ©2011-13 Thérèse Murdza. 
All rights reserved forever. And ever. xo
